The paper proposes a visual body-aware embedding that captures clothing's affinity with different body shapes, which involves computer vision techniques such as multi-view embedding. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques to learn the embedding from an online catalog, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as the second likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the importance of inclusion and diversity, which suggests cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the third likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to explain the algorithm's suggestions, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach using automated metrics and human opinion, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the fifth likely sub-category.
